##Li Tie: Take the opportunity of epidemic prevention and control to establish a new big data service system

I-CAIJING

As a result of the crisis, some big data companies on the Internet have been able to use new data sources to launch business and social services, and governments have been able to turn data services over to the market and create new ways of managing data sources, improve the efficiency and reduce the cost of dealing with urban and social governance, as well as all kinds of sudden crises

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
By Li Tie

The prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia epidemic, the main problem is faced with the risk of transmission of strict precautions. Because of the large scale and wide range of population movement, involving the whole country and even the international, how to track the potential spread of the virus population and obtain more accurate information is a severe test for all levels of municipal and local governments.

At present, most of the measures that can be seen are strictly defensive in the traditional way. They are closely managed through grass-roots communities, enterprises, institutions and organizations, and so on. Even enterprises and units will not hesitate to stop work and production, all people are required to live in homes of self-isolation and isolation. Some cities even require that only one person in each family be allowed to go out for two hours a day. These measures, to prevent the rapid spread of the epidemic, the role is very obvious, but also paid a huge social and economic costs.

Adjust the traditional mode of thinking, rely more on new technology and new sources of information

With the development of Information revolution and the Internet, many cities are pursuing the vision of modernization in the process of rapid urbanization, and have proposed the goal of establishing "information city" , "smart city" and "data city" , and invested huge sums of money, most cities now have data centers and information platforms.

However, in the cases of epidemic prevention and control that we have seen, how much role these platforms have played in monitoring and tracking the spread of the epidemic, there is still huge potential to be tapped. The reason is that the information platforms and data centres that were originally invested in are still using traditional data sources. In other words, the so-called data are from the government's internal agencies reported data. For example, the Census and sample data of the Bureau of Statistics, the reported data of various departments and enterprises, etc. .

These data have played an important role in supporting the annual analytical reports on economic and social development. But in the face of such a major public health security crisis across the country, these reported figures are too time sensitive to be useful. Because understanding the mobility and spatial location of the population, if you follow the traditional data sources, you have to mobilize the whole society again, which is very costly, and sourcing circumstances is very problematic. This shows that we are facing the rapid development of science and technology, the establishment of urban data centers and information platforms, the need to play a new source of information data.

The pressure of the rapid spread of the epidemic has reminded us that in the face of a series of problems such as future urban social governance and public health security, it is necessary to adjust the original thinking mode and rely more on new technologies and new information sources, in order to ultimately achieve the service for the whole society and all urban and rural residents.

What are new sources of information and data? In fact, it is the information source and data source based on the Internet, mobile data and the spatial location information of mobile phone signaling, which is formed by all individual users.

Put simply, every adult, including some children and teens, is hooked up to cell phones and the Internet. The location information of mobile phone is automatically generated, and various location in network consumption is adopted by network operators after personal authorization. These sources of information, based on each person's cell phone signaling and network data, also make up the so called most widely covered data source. The so-called big data, not only contains the traditional report information, more is to cover the whole society based on the Internet and mobile signaling data sources.

In the information sources and data sources, who has a wide coverage, data sources, who the greater the impact of social consumption, the future development of data potential is more prominent.

Taking epidemic situation as a turning point to establish a new data service system

According to statistics, the major Internet companies that currently have the advantage of Internet information sources are tencent, Alibaba, Baidu and Jd.com. In 2019, tencent had 991 million monthly active users on Wechat, and Alibaba had 785 million monthly active users on its mobile terminal, alipay has more than 650 million monthly active users; Baidu has 316 million monthly active APP users; Jd.com has 334 million active purchase users; and Douyin has 650 million monthly active users. China Mobile, China Unicom and China Telecom have the most mobile information sources, with 947 million, 321 million and 334 million mobile subscribers respectively, accounting for 59.2 percent, 20 percent and 20.8 percent of the country's mobile subscribers.

The Network Information Data and the handset signaling data are compared, in the daily application process, obviously is the network user has the superiority. A single internet company, such as tencent or Alibaba, can match China Mobile's size and reach a wide range of applications. But from the point of view of full coverage, especially in the epidemic spread of the crisis for the tracking of potential infected people, it is clear that the coverage of network data is weaker than the coverage of mobile phone users. Because for web users, a mobile phone can provide the location of many web services at the same time, but all web services are inseparable from the mobile phone. In other words, both tencent and alibaba account for 60-70% of China's population. But that's it. Even if the two are added together, the total number of users is still so that spatial location can not achieve full coverage. For mobile phone users, though, the total could reach more than 1.6 billion, more than the total population of China. But the mobile phone users of the three major operators can not overlap, even if there is a multi-phone phenomenon, it is difficult to change the overall size of users. It can be said that China Mobile, China Unicom and China Telecom's total mobile phone users, can basically cover all users in the country. In this sense, mobile phone users can achieve more than Internet users to achieve full coverage.

From the actual life can also see, except children, almost all adults are inseparable from mobile phones. Because mobile phone signaling can achieve full coverage of space and population, through the big data system of mobile phone signaling, it is possible to track the movement of population space in all directions. As long as the signaling data of the three major mobile phone operators are used as a whole, we can achieve real big data-based urban governance.

The tracking capability of the cell phone signaling can be used to continuously locate any owner, whether turned on or off, 24 hours a day. We can not only track the movement of individuals, but also the population of the city for data analysis.

For example, the number of people in a city in the past six months, which are foreign, which are local, through the real-name verification of mobile phone numbers, you can get results. Within half a year's data storage time, can be the flow of population, the accumulation of spatial location, to make accurate analysis. For the need of epidemic prevention and control, starting with mobile phone signaling, we only need to get the data from the three major operators. During the period of initial spread of the epidemic in Wuhan, how many mobile phone users were in Wuhan and how many were out-of-town mobile phone users, a clear picture of the size of the population and the specific population involved in the outbreak can be obtained.

If we want to know more about the spatial changes of these mobile phone users, we just need to take the mobile phone numbers of these out-of-town and local out-of-town people, especially the mobile information before the closure of the city, through the outbreak of key cities respectively reported to the headquarters of the three companies and sent to the local companies, the local can be based on these cell phone signaling data to monitor the whereabouts of people out of these areas at any time.

To do this, it will require the three mobile phone operators to mobilize grassroots companies across the country to provide accurate data sources, as well as relevant companies to run big data models and build tracking and monitoring systems for large populations. In this way, the final population flow and the track of the spread of the epidemic can be clearly obtained, providing the most accurate and effective data source for the prevention of the epidemic throughout the country.

In this way, we can greatly reduce the pressure of local governments, reduce social costs, and achieve effective and accurate epidemic prevention and control. On the basis of mobilizing the three major mobile phone operators, the governments at all levels can also request the local network operators to provide network information data to supplement the data sources of mobile signaling. This strengthens the ability to monitor data and prevent omissions.

Of course, for mobile phone operators and network operators, will increase the workload and investment. However, the government's general mobilization for epidemic prevention can be supported by special investment. Each enterprise also can the support to the disaster area, manifests in the data source support.

It is also undoubtedly the best opportunity for local governments at all levels. That is, we should use the disaster to rebuild the data service system for the whole society, reform the traditional data collection methods, and establish the Internet and information technology as the center, real big data systems based on user data sources. Integrating government information and data platforms. It has moved from being a service for the government to a service for society as a whole, especially one that can cope with all kinds of social crises that may arise.

For mobile phone operators and Internet companies, by integrating data sources, it really enlarges the channels through which data can be used, from the needs of the enterprise itself to the needs of social responsibility, make full use of long-deposited and even wasted data sources, and discover new business opportunities and social service opportunities in the process of full data coverage.

Some enterprises with the ability to provide data services can use this data integration for in-depth Research and development, to establish a new social public service and business services data information platform.

On the one hand, the central government can also effectively use mobile phone and network data sources to support the construction of enterprises'data repositories through the purchase of services during the epidemic crisis. Mobile phone operators and network operators, because data storage will take money and resources, most of the six months or at most two years to delete the past data. If the central government supports companies to build data repositories, it should be the best opportunity for mobile operators and network operators to regenerate and make unlimited use of data that has been idle and wasted for too long, a wider range of services can be provided for countries and cities as well as businesses of all kinds.

On the other hand, after the crisis, some Internet big data companies can set up new companies, use new data sources to launch business and social services, and the government can turn data services over to the market, develop new ways of managing data sources, improve the efficiency of responding to urban and social governance, as well as various sudden crises, and reduce costs.

(the writer is chief economist at the Center for Urban and small-town reform and development in China. Editor: Zhu Tao.)
